text.tspan: p90 vs p10 of income/consumption distribution: Average annual change
Change in the level of income/consumption per day that marks the cut-off point of the bottom 10% and top 10% of
the distribution. Figures refer to average annual growth between the first and last available observations for each
country. For some countries both income and consumption figures are shown.

Source: Our World in Data based on PovcalNet (2019)
